CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 2, 1954, pg. 2 reads: "African Student Finds Welcome - Kwamena Dougan, a virtually penniless native of the Gold Coast in West Africa, this week found a gracious welcome and unexpected generosity in his quest to become an electrical engineer. Here he is with Dr. James B. Woodford, assistant professor of electrical engineering, in one of the electronics laboratories at famed Carnegie Tech. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Kwamena Dougan, wearing patterned tie and zippered jacket with light colored collar, standing in interior with light colored walls and model airplane on shelf
